      • dsize

        public int dsize()
        Compute the number of data blocks in the file system. Will return 0 if the file system is uninitialized. The number of data blocks is the number of blocks in the file system minus the super block size (1), the number of inode blocks, and the number of freemap blocks.
        Returns:
        number of data blocks

      • mblock0

        public int mblock0()
        Compute the number of the first freemap block (returns 0 if there are no freemap blocks because the entire freemap fits in the SuperBlock).

        block number of the first freemap block
